          "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"sg-evals/expressjs-express\",\n      \"path\": \"lib/request.js\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"sg-evals/expressjs-express\",\n      \"path\": \"test/req.host.js\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"sg-evals/expressjs-express\",\n      \"path\": \"History.md\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"sg-evals/expressjs-express\",\n      \"path\": \"lib/request.js\",\n      \"symbol\": \"host\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The deprecated `req.host` property is referenced in three source files within the expressjs-express repository:\\n\\n1. **lib/request.js (lines 418-431)**: Contains the definition and implementation of the `req.host` getter. This is a deprecated property that parses the \\\"Host\\\" header field to a host value, with support for X-Forwarded-Host when \\\"trust proxy\\\" is enabled. The getter extracts the host from either the X-Forwarded-Host header (if trusted) or the Host header, handling comma-separated values and returning undefined if no host is present.\\n\\n2. **test/req.host.js**: Contains comprehensive test suite for the `req.host` property with 11 test cases covering:\\n   - Basic Host header parsing (lines 12, 25, 51, 64, 80, 96, 112, 128, 145)\\n   - IPv6 literal support (lines 51, 64)\\n   - X-Forwarded-Host support when trust proxy is enabled\\n   - Port number handling\\n   - Edge cases when Host header is absent\\n\\n3. **History.md**: Contains 7 changelog entries mentioning `req.host` fixes and features across multiple versions:\\n   - Added `req.host` property (initial introduction)\\n   - Added X-Forwarded-Host support to `req.host`\\n   - Fixed `req.host` when no Host is present\\n   - Fixed `req.host` for IPv6 literals\\n   - Fixed `req.host` when using \\\"trust proxy\\\" hops count\\n\\nAll three files contain genuine references to the `req.host` deprecated property as a standalone feature, not as part of `req.hostname`.\"\n}\n",
